data.chText: （衣服等上的）绒毛，蓬松毛团，尘团
data.enText: small pieces of wool, cotton, etc. that gather on clothes and other surfaces
soft animal fur or bird feathers, that is found especially on young animals or birds
entertainment that is not serious and is not considered to have great value
to do sth badly or to fail at sth

data.chText: 一个唾手可得的进球机会被他搞砸了。
data.enText: He completely fluffed an easy shot (= in sport) .

data.chText: 多数演员都会偶尔念错台词。
data.enText: Most actors fluff their lines occasionally.
to shake or brush sth so that it looks larger and/or softer
The female sat on the eggs, fluffing out her feathers.
Let me fluff up your pillows for you.

tr: a blunder (especially an actor's forgetting the lines)
something of little value or significance
ruffle (one's hair) by combing the ends towards the scalp, for a full effect
make a mess of, destroy or ruin
example: I botched the dinner and we had to eat out
the pianist screwed up the difficult passage in the second movement

value.def: Fluff consists of soft threads or fibres in the form of small, light balls or lumps. For example, you can refer to the fur of a small animal as fluff .

example.ex: ...the nestbox which contained two chicks: just small grey balls of fluff...
example.tran: 窝里有两只雏鸟：看上去还只是两个灰色的毛毛球

example.ex: She noticed some bits of fluff on the sleeve of her sweater.
example.tran: 她发现羊毛衫的袖口上起了一些毛球。

value.tran: (织物上的)绒毛，蓬松毛团;(小动物的)绒毛

value.def: If you fluff something that you are trying to do, you are unsuccessful or you do it badly.

example.ex: She fluffed her interview at Oxford.
example.tran: 她在牛津的面试搞砸了。

value.def: If you fluff things such as cushions or feathers, you get a lot of air into them, for example by shaking or brushing them, in order to make them seem larger and lighter.

example.ex: She stood up and fluffed her hair, wiggling her fingers through it and then throwing it back.
example.tran: 她站起身来，弄松了头发，将手指穿过发丝，然后把头发向后一甩。

example.ex: Take the pan off the heat and cover for 5 minutes to fluff up the rice.
example.tran: 把平底锅从火上拿开，焖 5 分钟让米饭变松软。

value.tran: 抖松(靠垫、羽毛等);使蓬松
